1
00:00:04,933 --> 00:00:08,933
Bulk scoring is a feature that helps users score multiple plots or subplots at the same time.

2
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:15,500
First open a trial in Field Scoring mode.

3
00:00:20,700 --> 00:00:24,700
Select a plot to view the bulk scoring options.

4
00:00:28,600 --> 00:00:32,600
The Subplot button displays all subplot-level traits. 

5
00:00:35,766 --> 00:00:39,766
The measurement you choose will be applied to all subplots in your selected plot. In this case, two.

6
00:00:48,800 --> 00:00:52,800
For scoring plot-level traits, choose any number of plots and select the Plot button. 

7
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:05,000
Any chosen values are applied to all selected plots.

8
00:01:11,533 --> 00:01:15,533
Continue choosing plots to bulk score.

9
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:29,000
Select the Overwrite Trait Values checkbox if you want to bulk score a trait that already has a value.

10
00:01:41,233 --> 00:01:45,233
You can also bulk score tags on any selected plot.
